{{Infobox person | name = Ram Soraya | residence = | other_names = Raam Soraya | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birthname = Raam Lalchand Pridhani | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1949|11|4}} | birth_place = [[Surabaya]], [[East Java]], [[Indonesia]] | deathdate = | deathplace = | deathcause = | nationality = | alma_mater = [[Institut Teknologi Sepuluh Nopember]] | yearsactive = | known = | occupation = Entrepreneur and film producer | title = | salary = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = [[Sunil Soraya]]{{Clear}}[[Rocky Soraya]] | relations = | website = | footnotes = | employer = | height = | weight = | callsign = | awards = | signature = }} '''Raam Lalchand Pridhani''' ({{lang-pa|ਰਾਮ ਲਾਲਚੰਦ}} aka '''Raam Soraya''' and '''Ram Soraya''') is an entrepreneur and film producer from Indonesia. He was born in [[Surabaya]], Indonesia, 4 November 1949. He is the owner of production house Soraya Intercine Films.
Before the film industry, he was a textile importer. His career in film began as a distributor for East Java (1972 to 1982). He became a producer in the ''[[Budak Nafsu]]'' (1983) which won Best Film at the [[Indonesian Film Festival]] (FFI) 1984. The movie is the result of his own company, PT. Soraya Intercine Films. After that he made films including ''[[Sembilan Wali]]'' (1985), ''[[Permainan Yang Nakal]]'' (1986), ''[[Saya Suka Kamu Punya]]'' (1987) and others.
Soraya's career peak came after taking over production of the [[Warkop DKI]] series from [[Raam Punjabi]]'s Parkit Film. Soraya made Warkop TV series in 1995 until 2007.
